Learning Microsoft Azure fully involves understanding a mix of cloud fundamentals, hands-on skills, and certifications. Here's a complete roadmap to help you go from beginner to advanced in Azure:

🧭 1. Cloud & Azure Fundamentals
Learn the basics of:
What is Cloud Computing?

IaaS, PaaS, SaaS

Regions & Availability Zones

Azure Portal and CLI

🎓 Recommended:
Azure Fundamentals (AZ-900) – great starting point

📘 Study Resources:
Microsoft Learn - AZ-900

Free Azure sandbox at Microsoft Learn

🏗️ 2. Core Azure Services
Learn the essential building blocks of Azure:

Compute: Azure VMs, App Services, Azure Functions

Networking: Virtual Networks, NSGs, Load Balancer, VPN Gateway

Storage: Blob, File, Queue, Table Storage

Databases: Azure SQL, Cosmos DB, Azure Database for PostgreSQL/MySQL

🛠️ 3. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
Learn how to manage Azure using:

Terraform or ARM Templates

Bicep (Azure-native IaC language)

🔐 4. Security & Identity
Azure Active Directory (AAD)

Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

Managed Identities

Key Vault

🧠 5. Monitoring, Logging, and Automation
Azure Monitor

Log Analytics

Application Insights

Azure Automation

🚀 6. DevOps on Azure
Azure DevOps (Repos, Pipelines, Boards, Artifacts)

GitHub Actions with Azure

CI/CD pipelines for deployments

☁️ 7. Advanced Services
Kubernetes: AKS (Azure Kubernetes Service)

Serverless: Durable Functions, Logic Apps

Data Services: Azure Synapse, Data Factory

AI/ML: Azure Machine Learning, Cognitive Services


